n a narrow worship of information becomes dogma, such that research comes to mean data mining and other languages become provincial “flavors” folded into an impoverished Globish, or global English.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aElectronic information resources. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aGoogle.  aKnowledge-based Society.  aculture.  ademocracy.  adigital library.  auniversalism.1 aCassin, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSyrotinski, Michael.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311072901640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823278091zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823278091423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823278091/original  a978-3-11-072901-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK